rough Fishman's own concluding sentiments, as well as by the comprehensive and up-to-date bibliography of over 1,000 titles of Joshua A. Fishman's work, compiled by his wife, Gella Schweid Fishman. Together, the contributions in this volume pay tribute to the life work of one of the world's most prolific and original scholars in the field of sociolinguistics -- the founder of what we refer to in this volume as Fishmanian sociolinguistics.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Apr 2022) 0aSociolinguistics. 0aSociolinguistique. 7aLANGUAGE ARTS & DISCIPLINES / Linguistics / Sociolinguistics.2bisacsh  aJoshua Fishman.  aSociolinguistics.  alanguage change.1 aCoulmas, Florian, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFishman, Gella Schweid, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFishman, Joshua A., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGarcía, Ofelia, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPeltz, Rakhmiel, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aPeltz, Rakhmiel, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSchiffman, Harold F., eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aSchiffman, Harold, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aZakharia, Zeena, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertMultiLingual Matters Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2015z978311066313608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertMultiLingual Matters eBook Package Backlist 2000-2014z978311060671340uhttps://doi.org/10.21832/978185359904040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781853599040423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781853599040/original  a978-3-11-060671